ITV.Tour.de.France.2014.Stage.16.Live.PDTV.x264-NX

Tuesday 22nd July 2014 ITV4
2pm to 4:30pm Live

Live coverage of stage 16 after the second rest day and the riders are faced with the longest stage of this year's Tour, 237.5km from Carcassonne to Bagneres-de-Luchon. The HC Port de Bales, location of Andy Schleck's yellow jersey-costing mechanical in 2010, is the last climb before the long descent to the finish, a finale that could favour a lone attacker like Rui Costa. Presented by Gary Imlach with analysis from Chris Boardman, commentary by Phil Liggett and Paul Sherwen with Ned Boulting the reporter at the roadside.
